# YouTube Notes App - Business Requirements

## What This App Does

This is a web application that converts YouTube videos into organized, readable notes. Users paste a YouTube link, and the system creates structured notes with key points, timestamps, and summaries.

## Who Will Use This App

- Students who want to study from educational videos
- Professionals who need to extract information from training videos
- Content creators who want to summarize their own videos
- Researchers who need to organize video-based information

## Core Business Value

- Save time by automatically extracting key information from videos
- Create searchable, organized notes from video content
- Make video learning more efficient and accessible

## User Types

### Guest Users

- Can see the homepage and understand what the app does
- Cannot create, save, or access any notes
- Must sign up to use the app

### Registered Users

- Can create accounts and log in
- Can create notes from YouTube videos
- Can view, edit, and delete their own notes
- Can translate notes to different languages
- Can download notes in different formats
- Can search and organize their notes

## Main Features (What Users Can Do)

### 1. User Account Management

**What users need:**

- Create new account with email and password
- Log in to existing account
- Log out from their account
- Update their profile information

**Business rules:**

- Each user must have a unique email
- Passwords must be strong and secure
- Users can only access their own notes

### 2. Create Notes from YouTube Videos

**What users need:**

- Paste a YouTube video URL
- Get automatically generated notes with:
  - Video title and channel name
  - Key points and main topics
  - Timestamps for important sections
  - Summary of the content

**Business rules:**

- Only valid YouTube URLs are accepted
- If video has no captions, show a message explaining the limitation
- Same video URL from same user should not create duplicate notes
- Notes should be saved to user's account automatically

### 3. View and Manage Notes

**What users need:**

- See a list of all their notes
- Search through notes by title or content
- Sort notes by date, title, or channel
- Open and read individual notes

**Business rules:**

- Only show notes that belong to the logged-in user
- List should load quickly even with many notes
- Search should find relevant notes based on content

### 4. Edit Notes

**What users need:**

- Edit the title of notes
- Add, remove, or modify key points
- Add personal comments or highlights
- Save changes to notes

**Business rules:**

- All changes should be saved automatically
- Keep a history of changes so users can undo if needed
- Only the note owner can edit their notes

### 5. Delete Notes

**What users need:**

- Delete notes they no longer need
- Confirm before deleting to prevent accidents

**Business rules:**

- Deleted notes should go to a trash folder first
- Users should be able to restore notes from trash
- Notes should be permanently deleted after 30 days in trash

### 6. Translate Notes

**What users need:**

- Translate notes to different languages
- Keep original and translated versions
- Switch between different language versions

**Business rules:**

- Show that translations are done by computer (not perfect)
- Keep the structure and timestamps in translated versions
- If original note is edited, translation should be marked as outdated

### 7. Download Notes

**What users need:**

- Download notes as files (PDF, Word, or text)
- Choose which format to download
- Get files that can be opened on their computer

**Business rules:**

- Files should look good and be easy to read
- Include video title, channel, and timestamps in downloads
- Support different languages in downloaded files

## Important Business Rules

### Data and Privacy

- Users own their notes and data
- When users delete their account, all their notes should be deleted
- Don't share user notes with other users

### Usage Limits

- Each user can create a reasonable number of notes per day
- Large files should be handled efficiently
- Prevent abuse of the system

### Quality and Transparency

- If a video has no captions, clearly tell the user
- If note quality might be poor, warn the user
- Always show when content is computer-generated

### International Support

- Support multiple languages for the interface
- Handle different text directions (left-to-right, right-to-left)
- Support special characters and emojis

## Success Goals

- Users should be able to create their first note within 2 minutes
- Notes should be accurate and useful
- Users should want to come back and create more notes
- The app should work smoothly even with many notes

## Future Features (Not Required Now)

- Smart highlighting of important quotes
- Chapter-based summaries
- Different note styles (bullet points, Q&A format)
- Sharing notes with other users
- Mobile app version
- Browser extension for YouTube

